In a saucepan over high heat, add the chicken broth, rice, salt, bring to boil, stir once, reduce to low heat. Cook until rice is rice is tender, approximately 4-5 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside. In saute pan over medium heat, add 2 tbs of olive oil. Add onion and garlic, saute for 3-4 minutes, make sure not to brown onion or garlic. In a mixing bowl, combine sauteed mixture, crab meat, fish sauce, chili sauce, the cilantro and the remaining salt (1/4 tea.). Gently fold together. Gently fold in rice, egg and olive oil and continue folding until well blended. Take this mixture and divide into 4 portions, make patty. Put breadcrumbs on plate to coat each patty. In a large saute pan, over medium high heat add the last Tab. Olive oil. Add crab cakes, saute, only turning once, cooking approximately 4-5 minutes on each side. (Trick: If bread crumbs browning too quickly, remove crab cakes from the pan and finish cooking in a 350 degree oven on a alum. foiled cookie sheet until completely cooked.)